    "notes": "Macau immigration is administered by the Public Security Police Force (CPSP/FSM). The 88-country exemption list is set by Chief Executive written instruction under Law No. 16/2021 and Administrative Regulation No. 38/2021. The page was last modified 2026-06-01 on the official Macau government portal. Stay limits by category: (a) 6 months — British citizens with British passport; (b) 3 months — Cyprus, Israel, Lebanon, New Zealand; (c) 90 days — EU/Schengen member state passport holders plus Albania, Andorra, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Brazil, Cape Verde, Croatia, Dominica, Egypt, Grenada, Japan, Morocco, Korea (Republic of), North Macedonia, Mali, Mauritius, Mexico, Moldova, Mongolia, Montenegro, Armenia, Serbia, Tanzania, Uruguay, Monaco; (d) 30 days — general rule for all other exempted nationalities; (e) 14 days — Brunei and Kazakhstan. Diplomatic passports (any nationality except USA) get unlimited stay. Six nationalities (Bangladesh, Nepal, Nigeria, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Vietnam) must obtain a Macau visa in advance through a PRC diplomatic mission per Chief Executive Written Instruction No. 165/2010, effective 1 July 2010. No e-visa or ETA scheme exists for Macau."
