    "notes": "Source is Appendix 9 of the Macao Yearbook 2025, published by the Government Communication and Public Relations Bureau (GCS) — an official Macau SAR government publication. The DSI Identification Services Bureau is cited as the authoritative body within the yearbook. Footnote key: (b)=visa on arrival; (c)=visa on arrival OR e-visa; (i)=Israel now requires ETA-IL from 1 Jan 2025; (k)=South Korea K-ETA currently suspended until 31 Dec 2025; (n)=New Zealand requires NZeTA; (u)=UK requires ETA from 8 Jan 2025. Several countries marked (a) may have changed their policy — DSI is following up. Lebanon listed under visa-on-arrival in yearbook as entry at airport. Qatar listed under visa_free (30 days, with conditions) and also has e-visa option. Israel and New Zealand and UK moved to eta category per their respective footnotes requiring online pre-travel authorisation. Bahrain: visa on arrival or e-visa per footnote (j). Azerbaijan: visa-free until 20 Jul 2025 per footnote (ah). Maldives: VOA (b). Sri Lanka: ETA recommended over VOA per footnote (h). French overseas territories included under their respective French categories per footnote (s)."
